{"name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots","instances":[{"typeNames":["Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot"],"name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots.instInhabitedSnapshot","className":"Inhabited"}],"imports":["Init","Init.System.IO","Lean.Elab.Import","Lean.Elab.Command","Lean.Widget.InteractiveDiagnostic"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/Snapshots.lean#L157-L163","name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots.compileNextCmd.withNewInteractiveDiags","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Snapshots.html#Lean.Server.Snapshots.compileNextCmd.withNewInteractiveDiags","doc":"Compute the current interactive diagnostics log by finding a \"diff\" relative to the parent\nsnapshot. We need to do this because unlike the `MessageLog` itself, interactive diags are not\npart of the command state. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/Snapshots.lean#L97-L163","name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots.compileNextCmd","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Snapshots.html#Lean.Server.Snapshots.compileNextCmd","doc":"Compiles the next command occurring after the given snapshot. If there is no next command\n(file ended), `Snapshot.isAtEnd` will hold of the return value. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/Snapshots.lean#L86-L86","name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots.server.stderrAsMessages","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Snapshots.html#Lean.Server.Snapshots.server.stderrAsMessages","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/Snapshots.lean#L78-L84","name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots.parseNextCmd","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Snapshots.html#Lean.Server.Snapshots.parseNextCmd","doc":"Parses the next command occurring after the given snapshot\nwithout elaborating it. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/Snapshots.lean#L71-L72","name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot.isAtEnd","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Snapshots.html#Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot.isAtEnd","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/Snapshots.lean#L66-L69","name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot.infoTree","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Snapshots.html#Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot.infoTree","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/Snapshots.lean#L63-L64","name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot.diagnostics","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Snapshots.html#Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot.diagnostics","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/Snapshots.lean#L60-L61","name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot.msgLog","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Snapshots.html#Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot.msgLog","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/Snapshots.lean#L57-L58","name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot.env","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Snapshots.html#Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot.env","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/Snapshots.lean#L54-L55","name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot.endPos","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Snapshots.html#Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot.endPos","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/Snapshots.lean#L42-L50","name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots.instInhabitedSnapshot","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Snapshots.html#Lean.Server.Snapshots.instInhabitedSnapshot","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/Snapshots.lean#L27-L40","name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Snapshots.html#Lean.Server.Snapshots.Snapshot","doc":"What Lean knows about the world after the header and each command. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/Snapshots.lean#L24-L24","name":"Lean.Server.Snapshots.dummyTacticCache","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Snapshots.html#Lean.Server.Snapshots.dummyTacticCache","doc":""}]}